Package com.cboe.interfaces.domain.product

Interface Summary
BaseProduct A product that is not dependent on any other product.
Commodity A product that specifies the terms used to buy or sell a real-world item.
Composite A product that is based on a collection of products.
Debt A product that gives the holder the right to receive specified payments for a specified period.
Derivative A product whose values are dependent on a single underlying product.
Equity A product which represents ownership of a company, for example, a common stock or a preferred stock.
Future A product that gives the holder the right to receive a given amount of the underlying product at a specified date.
Index A product that is the measure of the price of a collection of products.
LinkedNote A product that appreciates along with its underlying product, but preserves capital if the underlying product declines.
Option A product that gives the holder the right to buy or sell a fixed amount of a product at a fixed exercise price by exercising the option prior to its expiration date.
OptionType The contract type of an option, call or put.
PriceAdjustment A change to the value of a security that affects the prices of derivative products related to it.
PriceAdjustmentHome A home to create and find price adjustments.
Product Any financial product that is tradeable or underlies another product that is tradeable.
ProductAdjustment An update for a Product that is being changed as part of a PriceAdjustment.
ProductClass A collection of products of the same product type.
ProductClassHome A home class used to create or find product classes.
ProductComponent A part of a composite product.
ProductComponentHome A home for components of composite products.
ProductDescription A product description contains information about formatting of prices.
ProductDescriptionHome A home for product descriptions.
ProductDispatch A double dispatch mechanism for product types.
ProductHome A home to create and find products.
ProductType A means to maintain additional information about the available product types.
ProductTypeHome A home to create and find product type information.
ReportingClass A collection of products in the same product class that are grouped for reporting purposes.
ReportingClassAdjustment An update for a ReportingClass that is being changed by a PriceAdjustment.
ReportingClassHome A home for creating and finding reporting classes.
Strategy A product that represents a group of products being traded as a unit to control risk.
StructuredProduct A derivative product that is issued in limited quantities.
UnitInvestmentTrust A product that represents part ownership of a basket of products.
VolatilityIndex An index which measures the volatility of a product class.
Warrant A product that gives the holder the right to buy the underlying product at a specified price for a specified period.
